## Final checklist

Before you stop, confirm — `validate_render` covers manifest / entry-point / sqlId / relative-import contracts statically, so this list focuses on the rules it *can't* mechanically check:

- [ ] You glob'd `reports/*` before `start_new_report` (or `reports/*/manifest.json` before `bind_existing_report` when the user gave a display name).
- [ ] Numeric columns are coerced with `Number(...)` before arithmetic / Recharts.
- [ ] Loading / error states are rendered for every `useQuerySql` call.
- [ ] All hooks (`useRef` / `useMemo` / `useState` / `useCallback` / `useEffect` / `useQuerySql` / custom hooks) are declared as named `const`s at the top of every component — never called inline from JSX (e.g. `<div ref={useRef(null)}>`), all before any `if (...) return …`. Violations crash the artifact with React error #310.
- [ ] `validate_render()` returned `success: 1`.
